# forbidden.txt — master deny list (example template)
#
# Rename this file to `forbidden.txt` and customize for your private names.
# `forbidden.txt` itself is gitignored — never commit your real deny list.
#
# Format: one regex pattern per line. Case-insensitive (consumers use grep -iE).
# Lines starting with `#` and empty lines are ignored.
#
# Used by:
#   - global git pre-commit hook    — blocks any commit to public repo with a match
#   - lib/push-mirror/anon.py       — sanity-checks anonymized output after substitution
#
# Why two layers: anon.py rewrites known terms via replacements/<target>.md;
# the pre-commit hook is the catch-all for anything anon.py missed.

# --- Personal identifiers ---
# /Users/<your-username>
# <your-name>\.<your-surname>
# Your Full Name

# --- Private project names / product codes ---
# private-project-a
# private-project-b
# internal-codename

# --- Numeric identifiers (Asana/Notion/Slack/etc) ---
# 1234567
# 89012345
